<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-02-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-02-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="226" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d226">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.113/582</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by President Roosevelt for the Secretary of
                                State</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-23">February 23,
                                1935</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>After you get back will you speak with me about the advisability of a
                            message on war profits and kindred subjects. I enclose a memorandum, but
                            I do not know who it is from.<note n="1" xml:id="d226fn1">Undated
                                memorandum by Bernard M. Baruch, not printed.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>F[<hi rend="smallcaps">ranklin</hi>] D. R[<hi rend="smallcaps">oosevelt</hi>]</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>